Argentine ant
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:OED: . Argentine ant, a small brown South American ant, Iridomyrmex humilis,which has been introduced into and become a household and orchard pest in parts of the United States, South Africa, and elsewhere. 1908 C. W. WOODWORTH in California Agric. Exper. Station Circular No. 38, p. 1 (title)The Argentine Ant in California.
