Quote: DOC rangers recently returned to Whangarei Heads in Northland to combat an infestation of Argentine ants that last year threatened the high conservation values of the area.... Argentine ant populations will spread if left for any length of time, so the infestation could have expanded further into the Bream Head Reserve kiwi sanctuary, affecting conservation values and wildlife as well as becoming too expensive to deal with.
